<section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n="pick.eyebrow1">Function · Picking</p>
      <h1 data-i18n="pick.h1">The plan is built. <span class="lime">Execution is next.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead" data-i18n="pick.lead1">
        openWCS already plans the pick — allocation, cubing and batch planning are
        <span class="pill pill-built" data-i18n="pick.pill1">Built</span>. The operator-facing execution layer is
        <span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="pick.pill5">Roadmap</span>: planned and designed, not yet implemented.
      </p>
      <p class="status-line">⚑ Pick execution is planned — not yet implemented. Pick planning below is live today.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n="pick.eyebrow2">Built today</p>
        <h2 data-i18n="pick.h2">Pick planning that's live.</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pick.p1">
          Before anyone touches a tote, the hard decisions are made: what stock to commit, how it fits a
          container, and how to group lines into efficient work.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="pick.tag1">Allocation</div><span class="pill pill-built" data-i18n="pick.pill2">Built</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="pick.h6">Commit the right stock</h3>
          <p data-i18n="pick.p2">Orders are allocated to specific stock, respecting availability and the location model — so each line points at a real, reachable unit before work is released.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="pick.tag2">Cubing</div><span class="pill pill-built" data-i18n="pick.pill3">Built</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="pick.h7">Multi-size cubing</h3>
          <p data-i18n="pick.p3">Lines are fitted into containers across multiple carton/tote sizes, so the planner knows how many of which size a set of orders needs before it hits the floor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="pick.tag3">Batch planning</div><span class="pill pill-built" data-i18n="pick.pill4">Built</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="pick.h8">Group lines into work</h3>
          <p data-i18n="pick.p4">Batch-pick planning groups order lines into efficient pick work, the basis for wave / batch picking — the planning that execution will later drive against.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n="pick.eyebrow3">On the roadmap</p>
        <h2 data-i18n="pick.h3">Putting the plan into operators' hands.</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pick.p5">
          The execution layer — confirming picks, guiding operators, running goods-to-person stations — is
          designed but not built. Framed honestly so you know exactly where the line is.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="pick.tag4">Confirmation</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="pick.pill6">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="pick.h9">Confirm the pick</h3>
          <p data-i18n="pick.p6">Planned: operator and goods-to-person pick confirmation that closes out a planned line against what was physically taken. Not yet implemented.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="pick.tag5">Guidance</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="pick.pill7">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="pick.h10">Light / voice / RF</h3>
          <p data-i18n="pick.p7">Planned: pick-by-light, pick-by-voice and RF-gun guidance so operators are directed line-by-line. Designed for, not yet built.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="pick.tag6">GTP workflow</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="pick.pill8">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="pick.h11">Goods-to-person stations</h3>
          <p data-i18n="pick.p8">Planned: the full GTP-station workflow — presenting HUs, capturing the pick, releasing the carrier — on top of the ASRS retrieval that already brings units to the station.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

